rg/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.999999999947704, \"rank\": 3.76253788317717e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to The Hollywood Reporter, the stunt was secretly filmed earlier this year in March.\", \"from\": 1371, \"to\": 1465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1384, \"end\": 1406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hollywood_Reporter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7525010053636155e-45, \"text\": \"The Hollywood Reporter\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hollywood_Reporter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hollywood_Reporter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cruise, who has been attending various events at the Paris Games, including women's gymnastics qualifiers and swimming competitions, has expressed his enthusiasm for the event.\", \"from\": 1467, \"to\": 1643, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's awesome,\\\" Cruise said as per The Hollywood Reporter.\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1679, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hollywood_Reporter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7525010053636155e-45, \"text\": \"The Hollywood Reporter\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hollywood_Reporter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hollywood_Reporter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Great stories, great athletes.\", \"from\": 1703, \"to\": 1734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's incredible what they have to do, the sense of accomplishment,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1811, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The segment involvingCruiseis being orchestrated by production company Fulwell 73, which is also behind notable projects like Hulu's 'The Kardashians' and Adele's 2021 CBS special 'One Night Only'.\", \"from\": 1813, \"to\": 2010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1968, \"end\": 1973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adele\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.252173956518063e-15, \"text\": \"Adele\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adele\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adele\"}, {\"begin\": 1981, \"end\": 1984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS\", \"score\": 0.9999987462482424, \"rank\": 1.238058409005043e-06, \"text\": \"CBS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to The Hollywood Reporter, the Los Angeles segment will combine pre-recorded and live elements, adding a dynamic touch to the Olympic handoff.\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2163, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2024, \"end\": 2046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hollywood_Reporter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7525010053636155e-45, \"text\": \"The Hollywood Reporter\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hollywood_Reporter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hollywood_Reporter\"}, {\"begin\": 2052, \"end\": 2063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.999999999947704, \"rank\": 3.76253788317717e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Originally, there were plans for a large-scale celebration at Will Rogers State Beach, where the Olympic flag was to be ceremoniously handed over.\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2313, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, this plan was abandoned due to concerns from the Los Angeles Police Department regarding potential disruptions along the Pacific Coast Highway and difficulties in securing necessary permits from the California Coastal Commission.\", \"from\": 2314, \"to\": 2552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2372, \"end\": 2401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Police_Department\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Police Department\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Police_Department\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Police_Department\"}, {\"begin\": 2522, \"end\": 2551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Coastal_Commission\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"California Coastal Commission\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Coastal_Commission\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Coastal_Commission\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The closing ceremonies of the Olympics have traditionally featured grand and often celebrity-driven spectacles.\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2665, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2008 Beijing Games, for example, included a memorable performance by Jimmy Page and Leona Lewis on a faux bus en route to London.\", \"from\": 2666, \"to\": 2799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2739, \"end\": 2749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Page\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jimmy Page\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Page\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Page\"}, {\"begin\": 2754, \"end\": 2765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leona_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Leona Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leona_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leona_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 2792, \"end\": 2798, \"title\": \"http://d